The paper deals with improving PET image quality using deep neural networks, which is a computer vision task and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves training a deep residual convolutional neural network, which is a machine learning technique and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper formulates the objective function as a constraint optimization problem and solves it using the alternating direction method of multipliers (ADMM) algorithm, which is an optimization technique and falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves simulation data and hybrid real data, which are numerical analysis techniques and fall under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a multimedia computing task and falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
